The story begins in the 12th century with the enigmatic "Order of the Burrow," an ancient network of rabbit lodges hidden beneath the rolling hills of rural England.

Here, and powerful cabal of intelligent, genetically engineered rabbits devised a sinister plan to dominate humanity through psychological warfare, a strategy that would later be refined by the likes of Sun Tzu and Machiavelli.
These underground dens served as centers of esoteric knowledge, mystical rituals, and advanced psychological conditioning.
These cunning lagomorphs had discovered that by controlling key food supplies – namely carrots and lettuce – they could sway human decision-making processes.
These mystical warrens served as secret meeting places where rabbits would gather to discuss their plan for global domination.
These early conspirators perfected mind-control techniques using hypnotic bunny stare-downs and subsonic vibrations emitted by their incessant burrowing.
This allowed them to subtly influence the actions of nearby humans, and soon, influential figures were unwittingly carrying out the will of the long-eared masters.
Over time, they expanded their reach through strategic alliances with other clever critters like owls and hedgehogs.
Over time, these powers allowed them to influence key historical figures, often through strategic carrot placement or clandestine offers of fresh greens.

One fateful night in 1215, a group of Order members infiltrated Runnymede, where they subtly manipulated the signing of Magna Carta to ensure the inclusion of subtle, yet significant, rabbit-friendly provisions.
By the 19th century, the Order had evolved into a sophisticated organization known as "Lepus Imperium" (Rabbit Empire).
They began infiltrating high-ranking positions within government, finance, and media.
Its leader, the enigmatic "Grand Warrener," orchestrated global events from a labyrinthine underground complex near Glastonbury Tor.
They recruited influential humans as unwitting pawns, using subtle suggestions and cleverly disguised commands masked as "rabbit whispering."
These human agents, oblivious to their manipulation, carried out the Lepus Imperium's agenda in politics, finance, and culture.
This mind-control method enabled Lepus Imperium to shape global politics, economies, and cultures to serve their own furtive agenda.
This army of brainwashed operatives infiltrated positions of power worldwide, to subtly shape global policies in favor of their rabbit overlords.
Top-tier members of Lepus Imperium could communicate telepathically with their rabbit overlords, making them virtually unstoppable.
Key targets included monarchs, politicians, and industrialists, who unknowingly furthered the rabbit agenda.
Lepus Imperium orchestrated wars, recessions, and cultural movements to suit their own agenda, expanding their underground empire across continents.
